        Ruto faces the roar</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
      Summary: Protests across Kenya turn deadly amid anger over Ruto’s government policies. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      At least 16 people have died and about 400 are <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-spotlight-h2-3-injured-in-protests?source=website" target="_blank">injured in protests</a> across Kenya against President William Ruto’s government. Clinical groups confirmed gunshot wounds among the injured, including police officers. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        In Nairobi and other cities, protesters shouted “Ruto must go” while waving branches in a peaceful display of defiance. Authorities dispatched police and set up barricades to block entry to key sites, including the State House and parliament. President Ruto, speaking from Kilifi, asked protesters to remain peaceful, stating that Kenya has no other homeland.  </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       The government shut down live coverage of the protests, but Nairobi’s High Court overturned the directive and allowed three independent TV stations to air the news. The UN and independent rights groups deplored the violence and called for restraint.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         The demonstrations began on the anniversary of deadly protests in 2024, which were sparked by a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-spotlight-h2-4-controversial-tax-law?source=website" target="_blank">controversial tax law</a>. The steep taxes increased VAT on bread, annual taxes on cars, and affected basic health services. </p>
        </mj-text>
