       <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇮🇷 Iran - Internal crackdowns.</strong> 
           Following a ceasefire, Iran has intensified its internal crackdown, arresting over 700 people, executing alleged spies, and deploying troops, especially in Kurdish areas. Authorities are targeting suspected Israeli agents, separatists, and opposition groups like the Mujahedin-e Khalq (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-worldwide-6-domestic-despair?source=website" target="_blank">domestic despair</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇹🇻 Tuvalu - Australia flight.</strong> 
          Nearly one-third of Tuvalu’s population has applied for Australia’s recent climate visa, created under the 2024 Falepili Union. As rising seas threaten Tuvalu’s future, the annual visa provides 280 Tuvaluans a path to live in Australia. Experts warn the migration could drain Tuvalu of skilled workers, risking the island nation’s long-term viability (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-worldwide-7-climate-refugees?source=website" target="_blank">climate refugees</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇹🇭 Thailand - Reversing cannabis laws.</strong> 
           Thailand plans to reclassify cannabis as a narcotic just three years after legalizing it, threatening a $1B industry. The move follows a government split and growing concerns about unregulated use. The reversed law will ban recreational trades, requiring prescriptions for permissible cannabis use (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-worldwide-8-reverse-card?source=website" target="_blank">reverse card</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇪🇸  Spain - Court upholds Amnesty Law.</strong> 
          Spain’s Constitutional Court has upheld key parts of an amnesty law tied to the 2017 Catalonia independence crisis, pardoning over 300 people. PM Pedro Sánchez hailed it as a move toward unity. Critics argue it was a political agreement to keep Sánchez in power (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-worldwide-9-no-catalan-crackdowns?source=website" target="_blank">no Catalan crackdowns</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇪🇨 Ecuador - Captured gang leader.</strong> 
          Ecuador’s most wanted fugitive, Jose Adolfo Macias, alias "Fito," was recaptured in 2024 after escaping prison during a violent episode. Ecuador’s President Daniel Noboa confirmed his arrest in Manta, Fito’s hometown. Quito seeks his extradition to the US for gun and drug charges, following sanctions against his gang (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-worldwide-10-ecuador-s-most-wanted?source=website" target="_blank">Ecuador’s most wanted</a>). 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
