          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
     Why did Argentina opt out of BRICS+?
 
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/argentina-brics-membership-reassessment.jpg" alt="Argentina’s new government believes that the issue of the country’s accession to BRICS requires a more thorough scrutiny." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
          <i>Argentina’s government believes that the issue of the country’s accession to BRICS requires a more thorough scrutiny. Credits: Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Argentina did not join BRICS+ after the 2023 presidential election. Former President Alberto Fernández accepted the invitation to join the last wave of enlargement. He aimed to strengthen ties with China and Russia. He also sought funding from the BRICS New Development Bank. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        However, this quest was put on hold until further notice when Javier Milei was elected president. Milei, a libertarian with pro-Western views, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-jun-25-foundation-h1-11-rejected-the-invitation?source=website" target="_blank">rejected the invitation</a> in December 2023. He cited ideological differences and wanted to realign Argentina with Western democracies. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Milei has criticized authoritarian regimes, including China’s. He aims to reduce Argentina’s dependence on non-democratic nations. Still, he left the door open for future cooperation with BRICS+ members. He emphasized the importance of bilateral trade and monetary cooperation. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        This decision reflects a campaign agreement and a shift toward liberal economic policies. Argentina still faces economic challenges that require practical engagement with global partners, such as BRICS+, and not just the West. Public opinion in Argentina is very polarized on this issue.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
